genresAdvancedInfo.name: sheilat
genresAdvancedInfo.description: A genre of music from the Arabian Peninsula, sheilat is characterized by its use of the oud and the tabla. It is often played at weddings and other celebrations, and is known for its upbeat rhythms and lively melodies. Sheilat music is meant to be danced to, and is a popular form of entertainment throughout the region.
